external_knowledge:
- 'Wayward eateries' refers to food establishments with at least one violation;
- 'Regulatory infractions' refer to violations recorded during inspections;
- 'Hierarchy of their transgressions' refers to the total number of violations, with the most violations at the top.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT business_id) 
FROM inspections
WHERE score < 70;

external_knowledge:
- "faced the most scrutiny" refers to the businesses with the highest number of inspections;
- "watchful eye of the health department" refers to the inspections and follow-ups conducted by health inspectors;
- "frequency of inspections" is determined by the count of inspections each business has undergone.

- 'pass' inspections without follow-up requirements retain their original scores;
- 'pass' inspections with follow-up requirements have their scores reduced by 10;
- 'fail' or 'conditional' inspections have their scores reduced by 50;
- The comprehensive score is the average of the average scores for each cuisine type.
